---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Colophon"
  description="How hultan.com is built — type, palette, stack."
  prose
>
  <p class="eyebrow">Colophon</p>
  <h1>How this site is built.</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    Small site, opinionated stack. Restraint is the design principle and the
    build philosophy.
  </p>

  <h2>Type</h2>
  <p>
    Set in <a href="https://rsms.me/inter/">Inter</a> (variable, single
    weight axis) for prose and UI, with <a href="https://www.jetbrains.com/lp/mono/">JetBrains
    Mono</a> for dates, code, and editorial labels. System fonts as
    honest fallbacks.
  </p>

  <h2>Palette</h2>
  <p>
    Dark by default. Warm near-black background, birch off-white text, a
    single fjord-blue accent. Light mode is a mirror, toggled per session.
    All token pairs verified for WCAG AA contrast.
  </p>

  <h2>Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="https://astro.build/">Astro</a> for static generation.</li>
    <li>Markdown + MDX for content; Shiki (Vesper / min-light) for code.</li>
    <li>Plain CSS, custom-property tokens, no utility framework.</li>
    <li>Hosted on GitHub Pages with the custom domain <code>hultan.com</code>.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Source of truth</h2>
  <p>
    The design language lives in <code>/design.md</code> in the repo. If the
    code disagrees with the document, the document wins.
  </p>

  <h2>License</h2>
  <p>
    Site content © {new Date().getFullYear()} Andree Hultgren. Code is
    available on <a href="https://github.com/andreehultgren/andreehultgren.github.io">GitHub</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: var(--text-md);
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-4);
  }
</style>
